 to introduce basic concepts from deep learning in a rigorous mathematical fashion, e.g introduce mathematical definitions of deep neural networks (DNNs), loss functions, the backpropagation algorithm, etc. We attempt to identify for each concept the simplest setting that minimizes technicalities but still contains the key mathematics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aFaltungsneuronale Netze. 4aKünstliche Neuronale Netze. 4aMaschinelles Lernen. 4aTiefes Lernen. 7aCOMPUTERS / Intelligence (AI) & Semantics.2bisacsh  aMachine Learning, Deep Learning, Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs), Regression, Deep Neural Networks (DNNs),.1 aJabin, Pierre-Emmanuel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831110258030 cprintz978311102431840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311102555140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111025551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111025551/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK